#compdef copywrite
# =============================================================================
# copywrite — HashiCorp's "Utilities for managing copyright
#             headers and license files" — a Go CLI tool for
#             automating copyright-header insertion + license-
#             file validation across software repositories at
#             scale.  Distinguishing from `addlicense` (Google),
#             `licensei`, `reuse`, `licensecheck`, and similar
#             tools by:
#               - HCL-CONFIGURED: project metadata + per-tree
#                 rules live in a `.copywrite.hcl` file
#                 (HashiCorp's own HCL config language) loaded
#                 via knadh/koanf with HCL parser
#               - GITHUB-ACTIONS-NATIVE: built-in GitHub
#                 Actions annotations + RUNNER_DEBUG=1 auto-
#                 elevation of log level to Debug
#               - SUBCOMMAND TAXONOMY: 6 subcommands +
#                 report's 2 sub-subcommands covering init,
#                 audit-dispatch, debug, header insertion,
#                 LICENSE validation, and compliance reports
#               - DISPATCH SUBCOMMAND: bulk-audit multiple
#                 repos via worker pool with configurable
#                 concurrency, sleep cadence, branch + batch
#                 IDs
#               - HEADERS RECURSIVELY: walks directory trees
#                 with `bmatcuk/doublestar/v4` glob matcher
#                 inserting SPDX-compliant headers
#               - LICENSE FILE REMEDIATION: validates LICENSE
#                 file existence + correctness; can fix
#                 missing/incorrect files
#               - SUBSYSTEM-NAMED HCLOG LOGGER: uses
#                 hclog.New(...).Named("cli") for the CLI
#                 subsystem, with auto-color, COPYWRITE_LOG_
#                 LEVEL env-var, and GitHub-Actions debug-
#                 mode auto-elevation
#             Used by: HashiCorp engineering teams across
#             Terraform, Vault, Nomad, Consul, Boundary,
#             Waypoint, Packer + IBM Corp (post-Hashicorp
#             acquisition) for organizational-scale license
#             compliance.
#
# Author:  HashiCorp (now IBM Corp.) — original release 2022;
#          maintainer transitioned to IBM Corp. after the
#          2024 IBM acquisition of HashiCorp (file headers
#          read "Copyright IBM Corp. 2023, 2025").
# Source:  https://github.com/hashicorp/copywrite
#          https://github.com/hashicorp/copywrite/blob/main/cmd/root.go
#          https://github.com/hashicorp/copywrite/blob/main/cmd/*.go
#          https://github.com/hashicorp/copywrite/blob/main/go.mod
# CLI:     cmd/root.go — cobra-based subcommand tree with
#          PersistentFlag `--config` (.copywrite.hcl), and
#          per-subcommand pflag.FlagSet definitions.  Headline
#          library: hashicorp/go-hclog (NEW VARIANT — cobra is
#          well-documented across many Go completions).
# Library: github.com/hashicorp/go-hclog
#          ("hashicorp/go-hclog" — released 2017 by HashiCorp
#           as the IN-HOUSE STRUCTURED LOGGER for the entire
#           HashiCorp Go ecosystem.  Distinct from uber-go/zap,
#           rs/zerolog, sirupsen/logrus, and Go 1.21+ stdlib
#           log/slog by being:
#             1. Tightly integrated with `hashicorp/go-plugin`
