#                attribution
#             2. Hierarchical Named() subsystem loggers —
#                hclog.Default().Named("cli") creates a
#                "namespace.cli" sub-logger that inherits
#                config from the parent
#             3. Built-in AutoColor / ColorOff / ForceColor
#                modes for ANSI-aware terminals
#             4. Standard-library bridge — InterceptLogger
#                allows wrapping the global `log` package
#             5. JSON output mode for log aggregator
#                consumption — JSONFormat option flips entire
#                logger to JSON-line output
#             6. Logger.IsTrace/IsDebug/IsInfo/IsWarn/IsError
#                predicate methods for guard-clause filtering
#                (skip expensive log-message construction when
#                the level wouldn't emit)
#             7. Used internally by Terraform, Vault, Nomad,
#                Consul, Boundary, Waypoint, Packer, and the
#                entire go-plugin ecosystem.)
